This paper deals with the analysis of contributions made by anonymous users to Wikipedia using the Tor network. The paper focuses on the behavior and motivations of these users, and the impact of their anonymity on their contributions. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), which deals with the social and ethical aspects of computing. Other likely sub-categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), as the paper deals with issues related to privacy, trust, and community behavior in online environments.
